1|Object has more than one incoming sequence flow.|To converge sequence flows use an object of type "Non-exclusive Gateway (converging)" instead.@2 |Object has more than one outgoing sequence flow.|To split the process flow use an object of type "Non-exclusive gateway" instead.@3|The start event of a process which is not top-level (an event subprocess) must have a trigger defined.|In case of an event-subprocess choose the appropriate trigger in chapter "Event type". It is not allowed to use sequence flow between pools.|Ensure that objects connected with a sequence flow are in the same pool or in no pool at all. Flow objects are: Task, Sub-Process, Choreography task, Sub-Choreography, Start event, Intermediate event (sequence flow), Intermediate event (boundary), End event, Exclusive gateway, Non-exclusive gateway, Non-exclusive gateway (converging). To connect the data objects use the "Data Association" relation.@9|The target object of the association relation is not correct.|Check the target object of the association. If the source object is a message, the target may be only a Choreography Task, a Sub-Choreography or a Relation Node. To connect the data objects use the "Data Association" relation.@9|The target object of the association relation is not correct.|Check the target object of the association.
